Rusty Quill is a London-based UK entertainment production company and podcast network specialising in original content creation focused on high-concept <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Speculative_fiction" target="_blank">speculative fiction</a>. Our aims? To produce serialised narratives in as many media as we can (audio, webcomic, video or even traditional prose) as well as provide a platform for new and interesting voices/talent. Basically, if it sounds like a really cool idea but is difficult to explain, we are all over it!

All our regular content is free to view, listen to and share but we do also offer standard commission-based work on request and supporters of our Patreon will have access to special backer-only content. Check out <a href="http://rustyquill.com/commissions/">Commissions</a> or our <a href="http://rustyquill.com/support/">Support</a> options for more info.

Our first project was the <a href="http://rustyquill.com/rusty-quill-gaming/" target="_blank">Rusty Quill Gaming Podcast</a>, which launched in June 2015 to bring the adventures of the London Rangers to life, through a Pathfinder Actual Play tabletop roleplaying campaign. This was followed in March 2016 by our extremely popular horror anthology podcast, <a href="http://rustyquill.com/the-magnus-archives/" target="_blank">The Magnus Archives</a>, which details the supernatural cases under investigation by The Magnus Institute and its archivists.

Between our current offerings, we get over 100,000 episode downloads a month and are still growing! Plus we have a number of projects in development and look forward to bringing them to you as soon as they’re ready.
